{"type":"message","id":"84de838f","parentId":"3587e90b","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:13:17.826Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about something programmatically, mentioning that if I have a script, it should be radically simple. This seems to be a continuation of a previous conversation, but I don't have that context.\n\nLet me check if there's any recent memory or context that might help me understand what they're referring to.\n\nSince this is the start of a session, I should follow the AGENTS.md guidelines:\n1. Read SOUL.md - already loaded\n2. Read USER.md - already loaded\n3. Read memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. If in MAIN SESSION (direct chat with human): Also read MEMORY.md\n\nThis appears to be a direct chat (webchat, direct), so I should read the memory files to get context on what we were discussing.\n\nLet me check today's and yesterday's memory files, plus MEMORY.md.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"I need to check recent memory to understand what you're referring to. Let me catch up on context."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9ea5c404ba8d479c8aa18a0c","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_695c1cf7ba034dc3a17b0873","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-03.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9a07867792e94ddc9e0f959f","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-02.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":75,"output":269,"cacheRead":13824,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14168,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772511190046}}
