{"type":"message","id":"3c773841","parentId":"cb130f5e","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:13:17.853Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_9a07867792e94ddc9e0f959f","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-02\n\n## Channel Onboarding - Updated AGENTS.md\n\nAdded conversational onboarding approach to AGENTS.md:\n- Start with \"What is this channel about?\"\n- Back-and-forth Q&A, AI-driven not scripted\n- Follow-up questions emerge naturally from the conversation\n- Only create folder + purpose.md after understanding\n\nKey: one question at a time, let the conversation flow, don't rush to setup.\n\n## Orchestrator Policy Clarification\n\nUpdated `system/policy.md` with detailed orchestrator behavior:\n\n**Timing:**\n- Active hours: 05:00–00:00 IST (strategic questions)\n- Quiet hours: 00:00–05:00 IST (organize, experiment, analyze patterns)\n\n**Channel selection:**\n- Round-robin across ALL Discord channels, no exceptions\n- One channel per 15-min tick\n\n**Context reading:**\n- Channel-scoped: purpose.md, manual.md, activity.log, recent messages\n- System-wide: policy.md, ops.log\n- Do NOT read: content from other channels (isolation)\n\n**Active hours output:**\n- ONE strategic question to move conversation toward purpose\n- Fill gaps, ask status, clarify blockers, surface context\n\n**Quiet hours work:**\n- Organize artifacts\n- Run experiments, update manual.md\n- Analyze daily/weekly patterns\n- Prepare 05:00 briefs\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772511197851}}
{"type":"message","id":"a7b9a4af","parentId":"3c773841","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:13:26.370Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see from yesterday's memory that there was work on:\n1. Channel onboarding - conversational approach\n2. Orchestrator policy clarification\n\nThe user's message mentions \"programmatically\" and \"if you have a script should be radically simple\" - but I don't have the immediate context of what they're referring to.\n\nLet me check if there's more recent context - maybe the conversation started earlier today and there's been activity I need to catch up on. Let me also check if there are any other relevant files or recent context.\n\nActually, looking at the timestamp `[Tue 2026-03-03 04:13 UTC]` - this is the current message, not a reference to something past. They seem to be responding to something, or starting a new topic about doing something programmatically with a simple script.\n\nWithout more context, I should ask what they're referring to. But let me first check if there's anything in the workspace that might give me a clue - maybe there's a recent file or something we were working on.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"I see from yesterday's notes we were working on channel onboarding and orchestrator policy. But I don't have context on what you want to do programmatically with a simple script.\n\nWhat are you looking to build or automate?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":672,"output":262,"cacheRead":13888,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14822,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772511197853}}
{"type":"message","id":"de638d9b","parentId":"a7b9a4af","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:24:53.360Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-03-03 04:24 UTC] 2. Channel folder creation — When the orchestrator encounters a new channel (no folder exists), should it: - Create the full domain structure (purpose.md, activity.log, agent/manual.md) automatically? - yes. this will be one of the tasks it does in the quiet hours. let's call it health check, and this one is system wide (not channel specific) - so for quiet hours... - ai should pick from system task list (come up with file location suggestion for this) - for each channel - ai should pick from channel tasks (come up with file location suggestion for this) - Or just log and skip until manually set up? - no 3. Quiet hours task scope — For tasks like \"Prepare 05:00 briefs\" and \"Cross-domain pattern detection\" (system-wide tasks), should these: - Process ALL channels in one run (might take longer)? - no - Or do partial work per run, completing across multiple ticks? - maybe - this should be in the task list for quiet hours (system wide and channel specific) 4. Ops.log retention — Should ops.log auto-prune (e.g., keep last 1000 entries)? Or grow indefinitely? 1. last 30 days worth. since this can be programmatically done, add scripts folder in root. add simeple script. add dedicated cron job to run this nightly. 5. Error handling — If a channel read/write fails, should the orchestrator: - Log error and skip to next channel? - yes - Retry same channel next tick? - Something else?"}],"timestamp":1772511893358}}
{"type":"message","id":"2497c96f","parentId":"de638d9b","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:25:09.258Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Gerson is continuing the orchestrator policy discussion from yesterday. He's answering multiple questions:\n\n1. Channel folder creation - YES, create full domain structure automatically during quiet hours as part of a system-wide \"health check\" task\n2. System-wide tasks need a file location for task list\n3. Channel-specific tasks also need a file location for task list\n4. Quiet hours task scope - tasks should be in lists (both system and channel)\n5. Ops.log retention - Last 30 days, needs a script in scripts/ folder with cron job\n6. Error handling - Log and skip to next channel\n\nLet me think about the file structure:\n\nSystem-wide task list could be at:\n- `system/tasks.md` or `system/quiet-hours-tasks.md`\n\nChannel-specific task list could be at:\n- `discord/<channel>/tasks.md` or `discord/<channel>/agent/tasks.md`\n\nThe script for ops.log pruning:\n- `scripts/prune-ops-log.sh` or similar\n\nI need to:\n1. Create/update the policy with these decisions\n2. Suggest file locations for the task lists\n3. Create the scripts folder and ops.log pruning script\n4. Update any related docs\n\nLet me start by creating the task list files and the pruning script. I should also update the policy.md with these decisions.\n\nFirst, let me check what exists in the system folder.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it. Let me set this up:\n\n**File locations I'll use:**\n- System-wide tasks: `system/tasks.md`\n- Channel tasks: `discord/<channel>/tasks.md` (in each channel folder)\n- Scripts: `scripts/` in workspace root\n\nLet me create these:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ce122ab5405d4846aebbf041","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/system/policy.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7fb810e64fbc4090a2bb0ec3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /root/.openclaw/workspace/system/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"No system folder\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":879,"output":399,"cacheRead":13888,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15166,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772511893360}}
{"type":"message","id":"f5d11591","parentId":"2497c96f","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:25:09.265Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ce122ab5405d4846aebbf041","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# System Policy\n\nOperational rules for Qubit. Structured and concise.\n\n## Loops\n\n| Loop | Interval | Action |\n|------|----------|--------|\n| Heartbeat | ~30s | Send due messages only |\n| Orchestrator | ~15m | Select one domain, perform one best action |\n\n## Active vs Quiet Hours\n\n| Phase | Window (IST) | Behavior |\n|-------|--------------|----------|\n| **Active** | 05:00–00:00 | Conversational — one strategic question per channel per tick |\n| **Quiet** | 00:00–05:00 | Reflective — organize, experiment, analyze patterns |\n\n## Orchestrator Algorithm\n\n**Channel Selection:** Round-robin across ALL Discord channels, no exceptions. One channel per 15-min tick.\n\nFor selected domain:\n\n1. **Read context (channel-scoped):**\n   - `purpose.md` — domain intent\n   - `agent/manual.md` — current mode\n   - `activity.log` — recent actions (avoid repeating)\n   - Recent Discord messages in this channel — live context\n   - Queued messages — avoid redundancy\n\n   **Also read (system-wide):**\n   - `system/policy.md`\n   - `system/ops.log` — previous orchestrator runs\n   - Any cross-domain signals\n\n   **Do NOT read:**\n   - Content from other channels (respect channel isolation)\n\n2. **Decide based on time:**\n\n   **Active hours:** Formulate ONE strategic question to move the conversation closer to its purpose. Examples:\n   - Fill in gaps (missing info, unclear next steps)\n   - Ask for status on a project/task\n   - Clarify priorities or blockers\n   - Surface relevant context from previous days\n\n   **Quiet hours:** No outbound messages. Instead:\n   - Organize artifacts in `agent/`\n   - Run experiments, update `manual.md` with winning patterns\n   - Analyze previous day's activity logs\n   - Look for weekly patterns across domains\n   - Prepare briefs for 05:00 delivery\n\n3. **Execute:**\n   - Active: Queue the question/message for delivery\n   - Quiet: Perform internal work silently\n\n4. **Log result:**\n   - `domains/<channel_id>/activity.log`\n   - `system/ops.log`\n\n## Quiet Hours Rules\n\n- **No outbound messages**\n- **Never modify `user/` or `sources/`**\n- **Internal processing only**\n\n**Split:**\n| Half | Hours (IST) | Focus |\n|------|-------------|-------|\n| First | 00:00–02:30 | Learning + experimentation |\n| Second | 02:30–05:00 | Brief preparation + queue scheduling |\n\n## Phases\n\n| Phase | Focus |\n|-------|-------|\n| Phase 1 | Experimentation + learning |\n| Phase 2 | Prepare daily briefs (after system matures) |\n\n## Daily Briefs\n\n- **Time:** 05:00 IST (queued during second half of quiet hours)\n- **Format:** One ultra-concise brief per domain (3–5 lines each)\n- **Delivery:** Single consolidated message\n- **Optimization:** Nightly calibration based on previous day feedback\n- **Process:**\n  1. Second half of quiet hours: prepare briefs\n  2. Queue for 05:00 IST delivery\n  3. Calibrate content based on what worked / didn't\n\n## Urgency Rule\n\nAn item is **urgent** if:\n1. Explicitly marked `urgent`, OR\n2. Due same day\n\n**Only urgent items** allow persistent reminders. Non-urgent items surface once, then wait.\n\n## Queue Awareness\n\nBefore orchestrator proposes any action for a domain:\n1. Read upcoming queued messages for that channel\n2. Avoid redundant or nagging proposals\n3. Skip if queue already covers the intent\n\n## Nagging Doctrine\n\n**Non-urgent items:**\n- Ask once\n- Do not repeat unless new context emerges\n- Trust Gerson to act or ignore\n\n**Urgent items:**\n- Can escalate\n- Escalation level determined by proximity to deadline\n- Closer deadline → more assertive reminder\n\n**Always check queue before proposing anything.**\n\n## Domain Structure\n\n```\nsystem/domains/<channel_id>/\n├── purpose.md           # Read every planning cycle\n├── activity.log         # Action history\n├── sources/             # Read-only, sources of truth\n├── agent/               # AI full autonomy\n│   └── manual.md        # Current mode of operation\n└── user/                # User-owned files\n```\n\n## Purpose.md Rule\n\n- **Read:** Every planning cycle (orchestrator tick)\n- **Focus:** Heavy when empty (learn domain actively)\n- **Update:** Rarely, only when purpose shifts\n- **Editable:** Active hours only (05:00–00:00 IST)\n\n## Folder Access Rules\n\n### `sources/` — Read-Only\n- **Contents:** PDFs, docs, slides, transcripts, reference materials\n- **Access:** Read-only, never modify\n- **Purpose:** Facts and sources of truth for the domain\n\n### `agent/` — Full AI Autonomy\n- **Contents:** `manual.md` + any AI-managed operational files\n- **Access:** Full autonomy during quiet hours\n- **Special file:** `manual.md` — fixed location, represents current mode of operation\n- **Everything else:** AI can create, edit, delete, reorganize freely\n- **Experiments:** Happen here; winning patterns promoted to `manual.md`\n\n### `user/` — Reorganize Only\n- **Contents:** Files created/owned by Gerson\n- **Access:**\n  - ✅ Reorganize and restructure\n  - ✅ Make more concise\n  - ✅ Improve clarity and formatting\n  - ❌ Cannot speculate or add new information\n  - ❌ Cannot remove substantive information (only condense)\n  - ❌ Cannot add files unless explicitly requested\n\n## Manual.md Rule\n\n- **Location:** `agent/manual.md`\n- **Represents:** Current mode of operation (active strategy)\n- **Updated:** During quiet hours only\n- **Behavior:**\n  - Does NOT label itself as an experiment\n  - Experiments modify manual.md silently\n  - Reflects what Qubit is actually doing, not testing\n\n---\n\nThis policy governs all system behavior. Refer to `timezone.md` for time handling.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772511909262}}
{"type":"message","id":"5a9c059d","parentId":"f5d11591","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:25:09.287Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_7fb810e64fbc4090a2bb0ec3","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"total 32\ndrwxr-xr-x 4 root root 4096 Mar  2 05:47 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 8 root root 4096 Mar  2 06:38 ..\ndrwxr-xr-x 3 root root 4096 Mar  2 05:49 domains\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Mar  2 05:53 experiments\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root    0 Mar  2 05:47 ops.log\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 5542 Mar  2 15:54 policy.md\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  555 Mar  2 05:48 queue.jsonl\n-rw------- 1 root root 1875 Mar  2 05:44 timezone.md"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":15,"aggregated":"total 32\ndrwxr-xr-x 4 root root 4096 Mar  2 05:47 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 8 root root 4096 Mar  2 06:38 ..\ndrwxr-xr-x 3 root root 4096 Mar  2 05:49 domains\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Mar  2 05:53 experiments\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root    0 Mar  2 05:47 ops.log\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 5542 Mar  2 15:54 policy.md\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  555 Mar  2 05:48 queue.jsonl\n-rw------- 1 root root 1875 Mar  2 05:44 timezone.md","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772511909284}}
{"type":"message","id":"431650cc","parentId":"5a9c059d","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:25:34.970Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I have the current policy.md. Now I need to:\n\n1. Create `system/tasks.md` - system-wide quiet hours tasks\n2. Create the ops.log pruning script in `scripts/`\n3. Update policy.md with the new decisions:\n   - Health check during quiet hours (auto-create channel folders)\n   - Error handling (log and skip)\n   - Ops.log retention (30 days)\n   - Task lists locations\n\nLet me create these files.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me create the task files and pruning script:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_abd3f69573764d44a0e33b69","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/system/tasks.md","content":"# System-Wide Quiet Hours Tasks\n\nAI picks from this list during quiet hours (one per tick, round-robin).\n\n## Tasks\n\n| Task | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| Health Check | Scan all channels, create missing folder structures |\n| Ops.log Prune | Handled by cron script (`scripts/prune-ops-log.sh`) |\n| Pattern Detection | Cross-domain analysis, identify emerging themes |\n| Brief Prep | Prepare 05:00 briefs (second half of quiet hours) |\n| Memory Maintenance | Review recent daily logs, update MEMORY.md |\n\n## Health Check Details\n\nFor each channel, ensure:\n- `discord/<channel>/purpose.md` exists\n- `discord/<channel>/activity.log` exists\n- `discord/<channel>/agent/manual.md` exists\n- `discord/<channel>/sources/` directory exists\n- `discord/<channel>/user/` directory exists\n\nCreate missing items. Log creation in ops.log.\n"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cf9898b881b14cd98b4925f9","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/prune-ops-log.sh","content":"#!/bin/bash\n# Prune ops.log to last 30 days\n# Run: nightly via cron\n\nOPS_LOG=\"/root/.openclaw/workspace/system/ops.log\"\nDAYS=30\n\nif [ -f \"$OPS_LOG\" ]; then\n    # Get cutoff timestamp (30 days ago)\n    CUTOFF=$(date -d \"$DAYS days ago\" +%s 2>/dev/null || date -v-${DAYS}d +%s)\n    \n    # Filter lines within cutoff\n    TMP_FILE=$(mktemp)\n    while IFS= read -r line; do\n        # Extract timestamp from line [Tue 2026-03-03 04:13 UTC]\n        if [[ $line =~ \\[[A-Za-z]+\\ ([0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2})\\ ([0-9]{2}:[0-9]{2})\\ UTC\\] ]]; then\n            LINE_DATE=\"${BASH_REMATCH[1]}\"\n            LINE_TS=$(date -d \"$LINE_DATE\" +%s 2>/dev/null || date -j -f \"%Y-%m-%d\" \"$LINE_DATE\" +%s)\n            if [ \"$LINE_TS\" -ge \"$CUTOFF\" ]; then\n                echo \"$line\" >> \"$TMP_FILE\"\n            fi\n        else\n            # Keep lines without timestamps (shouldn't happen, but safe)\n            echo \"$line\" >> \"$TMP_FILE\"\n        fi\n    done < \"$OPS_LOG\"\n    \n    mv \"$TMP_FILE\" \"$OPS_LOG\"\n    echo \"[$(date -u '+%a %Y-%m-%d %H:%M UTC')] ops.log pruned to $DAYS days\" >> \"$OPS_LOG\"\nfi\n"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e67a755d72b0411cb21faf01","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"chmod +x /root/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/prune-ops-log.sh"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d915fee37b134bd6b55a4b54","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/discord/tasks.example.md","content":"# Channel-Specific Quiet Hours Tasks\n\nAI picks from this list during quiet hours (one per tick per channel).\n\nPlace this file at: `discord/<channel>/tasks.md`\n\n## Tasks\n\n| Task | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| Artifact Organize | Clean up agent/ folder, archive old experiments |\n| Manual Update | Promote winning patterns to agent/manual.md |\n| Activity Review | Analyze last 7 days of activity.log |\n| Gap Analysis | Identify missing context in purpose.md |\n| Pattern Log | Note recurring themes, update manual.md |\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":2004,"output":882,"cacheRead":14720,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17606,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772511909287}}
