{"type":"message","id":"4108ab65","parentId":"d7b6fff7","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:34:23.501Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need a different approach. Let me look at what Discord channels the bot has access to. Perhaps I can find the guild ID in a log or config file, or I can try sending a test message to one of the known channels.\n\nActually, looking at the folders in discord/, I see:\n- bytebles\n- knights-of-st-joseph\n- santa-casa\n\nThese are channel names. But I need channel IDs to use the Discord API. Let me check if there's a mapping somewhere.\n\nAlternatively, I can build the health check to:\n1. Use the folder names as the source of truth\n2. Create missing structure for each existing folder\n3. Log to ops.log\n\nBut that's not complete - it won't detect NEW channels that don't have folders yet.\n\nLet me ask the user for the guild ID, or try to find it another way.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d3e4072d449144309c1eaf3d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"guild\\|channel.*id\\|bytebles\\|santa-casa\\|knights\" /root/.openclaw/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"node_modules\\|\\.git\\|Binary\" | head -30"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":119,"output":245,"cacheRead":23424,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23788,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772512453395}}
{"type":"message","id":"dd544c72","parentId":"4108ab65","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:34:23.532Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_d3e4072d449144309c1eaf3d","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/root/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/c3de8854-78a0-40e2-a940-6401a7ec87eb.jsonl:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"dd4739f0\",\"parentId\":\"75ab47c4\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T15:46:06.494Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"message_id\\\": \\\"1478055805797535895\\\",\\n  \\\"sender_id\\\": \\\"729703087031320577\\\",\\n  \\\"conversation_label\\\": \\\"Guild #bytebles channel id:1478055780409278464\\\",\\n  \\\"sender\\\": \\\"729703087031320577\\\",\\n  \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"Mon 2026-03-02 15:46 UTC\\\",\\n  \\\"group_subject\\\": \\\"#bytebles\\\",\\n  \\\"group_channel\\\": \\\"#bytebles\\\",\\n  \\\"group_space\\\": \\\"1475377083667583019\\\",\\n  \\\"is_group_chat\\\": true\\n}\\n```\\n\\nSender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"9ers0n\\\",\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"9ers0n\\\",\\n  \\\"username\\\": \\\"9ers0n\\\",\\n  \\\"tag\\\": \\\"9ers0n\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nonboard this channel\"}],\"timestamp\":1772466366493}}\n/root/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/c3de8854-78a0-40e2-a940-6401a7ec87eb.jsonl:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"ffc96394\",\"parentId\":\"dd4739f0\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T15:46:13.985Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"The user is asking to \\\"onboard this channel.\\\" Looking at the context, this is a Discord channel called \\\"#bytebles\\\". According to AGENTS.md, there's a specific section about Discord Channel Onboarding:\\n\\n```\\n### 🆕 Discord Channel Onboarding\\n\\nWhen Gerson asks to onboard a Discord channel, it's about organizing the space — not audience analysis.\\n\\n**Do:**\\n- Ask what the channel is for (topic/project/context)\\n- Create `discord/<channel-name>/purpose.md` with a brief description\\n- Keep it lightweight — it's just metadata for me to remember context\\n\\n**Don't:**\\n- Ask about \\\"who's in this channel\\\" — it's always just us\\n- Overcomplicate the setup\\n```\\n\\nSo I need to:\\n1. Ask what the channel is for\\n2. Create `discord/bytebles/purpose.md` with a brief description\\n3. Keep it lightweight\\n\\nI should ask Gerson what this #bytebles channel is about so I can set it up properly.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"reasoning_content\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Got it! Let's onboard the **#bytebles** channel.\\n\\nWhat is this channel for? (topic/project/context)\"}],\"api\":\"openai-completions\",\"provider\":\"zai\",\"model\":\"glm-5\",\"usage\":{\"input\":6530,\"output\":238,\"cacheRead\":8576,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":15344,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1772466366494}}\n/root/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/c3de8854-78a0-40e2-a940-6401a7ec87eb.jsonl:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"c91ac06b\",\"parentId\":\"ffc96394\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T15:46:56.857Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"message_id\\\": \\\"1478056018830430359\\\",\\n  \\\"sender_id\\\": \\\"729703087031320577\\\",\\n  \\\"conversation_label\\\": \\\"Guild #bytebles channel id:1478055780409278464\\\",\\n  \\\"sender\\\": \\\"729703087031320577\\\",\\n  \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"Mon 2026-03-02 15:46 UTC\\\",\\n  \\\"group_subject\\\": \\\"#bytebles\\\",\\n  \\\"group_channel\\\": \\\"#bytebles\\\",\\n  \\\"group_space\\\": \\\"1475377083667583019\\\",\\n  \\\"is_group_chat\\\": true\\n}\\n```\\n\\nSender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"9ers0n\\\",\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"9ers0n\\\",\\n  \\\"username\\\": \\\"9ers0n\\\",\\n  \\\"tag\\\": \\\"9ers0n\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nI teach