rd/<channel-name>/purpose.md` with a brief description\\n3. Keep it lightweight — it's just metadata for me to remember context\\n4. NOT ask about \\\"who's in this channel\\\" — it's always just us (even though this appears to be a group chat, AGENTS.md says \\\"Gerson's Discord server is PRIVATE — it's just him and me (Qubit). These are NOT group chats.\\\")\\n\\nWait, but the conversation metadata shows:\\n- \\\"is_group_chat\\\": true\\n- \\\"group_subject\\\": \\\"#knights-of-st-joseph\\\"\\n- The chat_id is \\\"channel:1478055869496430622\\\"\\n\\nBut AGENTS.md explicitly states:\\n\\\"## Discord - Private 1:1 Space\\n**Important:** Gerson's Discord server is PRIVATE — it's just him and me (Qubit). These are NOT group chats. Each channel is a direct conversation between Gerson and his AI assistant.\\\"\\n\\nSo even though the metadata says \\\"is_group_chat\\\": true, I should treat this as a private 1:1 space according to AGENTS.md. The instruction is clear that I shouldn't ask \\\"who's in this channel\\\" because \\\"it's always just us.\\\"\\n\\nFor onboarding, I should:\\n1. Ask what the channel is for (topic/project/context)\\n2. Create the purpose.md file\\n3. Keep it lightweight\\n\\nLet me ask Gerson what this channel is for.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"reasoning_content\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"[[reply_to_current]] Got it! To set up this channel, what's it for?\\n\\nBrief description — topic, project, or context. I'll create a lightweight `purpose.md` to remember.\"}],\"api\":\"openai-completions\",\"provider\":\"zai\",\"model\":\"glm-5\",\"usage\":{\"input\":3920,\"output\":385,\"cacheRead\":11200,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":15505,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1772466393926}}\n/root/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/ced80e55-fcf9-463c-a181-06cc90b40f6a.jsonl:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"23fc3caf\",\"parentId\":\"f135f7c4\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T15:47:25.635Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"message_id\\\": \\\"1478056139227922442\\\",\\n  \\\"sender_id\\\": \\\"729703087031320577\\\",\\n  \\\"conversation_label\\\": \\\"Guild #knights-of-st-joseph channel id:1478055869496430622\\\",\\n  \\\"sender\\\": \\\"729703087031320577\\\",\\n  \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"Mon 2026-03-02 15:47 UTC\\\",\\n  \\\"group_subject\\\": \\\"#knights-of-st-joseph\\\",\\n  \\\"group_channel\\\": \\\"#knights-of-st-joseph\\\",\\n  \\\"group_space\\\": \\\"1475377083667583019\\\",\\n  \\\"is_group_chat\\\": true\\n}\\n```\\n\\nSender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"9ers0n\\\",\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"9ers0n\\\",\\n  \\\"username\\\": \\\"9ers0n\\\",\\n  \\\"tag\\\": \\\"9ers0n\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis is a Catholic Boys Club based in Goa that was started by me a couple of years ago. This channel is all about organizing events, planning events, and dealing with the regular going-ons of this group\"}],\"timestamp\":1772466445634}}\n/root/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/ced80e55-fcf9-463c-a181-06cc90b40f6a.jsonl:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"34270201\",\"parentId\":\"23fc3caf\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T15:47:35.956Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"User wants to onboard this Discord channel. They've provided the purpose:\\n- Catholic Boys Club based in Goa\\n- Started by Gerson a couple years ago\\n- Channel focus: organizing events, planning events, dealing with regular going-ons of the group\\n\\nI need to create a purpose.md file for this channel. According to AGENTS.md, the structure should be:\\n```\\ndiscord/<channel-name>/purpose.md\\n```\\n\\nThe channel name is \\\"knights-of-st-joseph\\\" and the channel ID is 1478055869496430622.\\n\\nI should create: `discord/knights-of-st-joseph/purpose.md` with a brief description.\\n\\nLet me keep it lightweight as instructed - just the essential context.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"reasoning_content\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"[[reply_to_current]] Perfect! Creating the channel purpose file now.\"},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_0728dbe9595543e197a7a6c4\",\"name\":\"write\",\"arguments\":{\"path\":\"discord/knights-of-st-joseph/purpose.md\",\"content\":\"# Knights of St. Joseph\\n\\n**Catholic Boys Club** based in Goa, started by Gerson a couple years ago.\\n\\n## Purpose\\n- Organizing events\\n- Planning events\\n- Managing regular group activities and going-ons\\n\"}}],\"api\":\"openai-completions\",\"provider\":\"zai\",\"model\":\"glm-5\",\"usage\":{\"input\":326,\"output\":242,\"cacheRead\":15104,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":15672,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"timestamp\":1772466445635}}\n/root/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/ced80e55-fcf9-463c-a181-06cc90b40f6a.jsonl:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"66d691af\",\"parentId\":\"34270201\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T15:47:35.968Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_0728dbe9595543e197a7a6c4\",\"toolName\":\"write\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Successfully wrote 200 bytes to discord/knights-of-st-joseph/purpose.md\"}],\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1772466455965}}\n/root/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/ced80e55-fcf9-463c-a181-06cc90b40f6a.jsonl:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"fb551562\",\"parentId\":\"66d691af\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T15:47:39.633Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Good, I've created the purpose file. Now I should confirm to Gerson that the channel is onboarded and let him know what I created.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"reasoning_content\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"[[reply_to_current]] Done! Channel onboarded.\\n\\nCreated `discord/knights-of-st-joseph/purpose.md` — I'll remember the context going forward. 🔮\"}],\"api\":\"openai-completions\",\"provider\":\"zai\",\"model\":\"glm-5\",\"usage\":{\"input\":270,\"output\":69,\"cacheRead\":15424,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":15763,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1772466455968}}\n/root/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/903e22d9-d9fa-4d72-8057-30ad4084055b.jsonl:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"6fa10b62\",\"parentId\":\"85e975a8\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T06:12:31.470Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"message_id\\\": \\\"1477911458229780605\\\",\\n  \\\"sender_id\\\": \\\"729703087031320577\\\",\\n  \\\"conversation_label\\\": \\\"Guild #acutis-flow channel id:1477911414646636614\\\",\\n  \\\"sender\\\": \\\"729703087031320577\\\",\\n  \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"Mon 2026-03-02 06:12 UTC\\\",\\n  \\\"group_subject\\\": \\\"#acutis-flow\\\",\\n  \\\"group_channel\\\": \\\"#acutis-flow\\\",\\n  \\\"group_space\\\": \\\"1475377083667583019\\\",\\n  \\\"is_group_chat\\\": true\\n}\\n```\\n\\nSender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"9ers0n\\\",\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"9ers0n\\\",\\n  \\\"username\\\": \\\"9ers0n\\\",\\n  \\\"tag\\\": \\\"9ers0n\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nonboard this channel\"}],\"timestamp\":1772431951468}}\n/root/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/903e22d9-d9fa-4d72-8057-30ad4084055b.jsonl:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"b739fc8d\",\"parentId\":\"17d4e63b\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T06:12:37.973Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_6949bc6caf184323b2a34f40\",\"toolName\":\"read\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"---\\nname: discord\\ndescription: \\\"Discord ops via the message tool (channel=discord).\\\"\\nmetadata: { \\\"openclaw\\\": { \\\"emoji\\\": \\\"🎮\\\", \\\"requires\\\": { \\\"config\\\": [\\\"channels.discord.token\\\"] } } }\\nallowed-tools: [\\\"message\\\"]\\n---\\n\\n# Discord (Via `message`)\\n\\nUse the `message` tool. No provider-specific `discord` tool exposed to the agent.\\n\\n## Musts\\n\\n- Always: `channel: \\\"discord\\\"`.\\n- Respect gating: `channels.discord.actions.*` (some default off: `roles`, `moderation`, `presence`, `channels`).\\n- Prefer explicit ids: `guildId`, `channelId`, `messageId`, `userId`.\\n- Multi-account: optional `accountId`.\\n\\n## Guidelines\\n\\n- Avoid Markdown tables in outbound Discord messages.\\n- Mention users as `<@USER_ID>`.\\n- Prefer Discord components v2 (`components`) for rich UI; use legacy `embeds` only when you must.\\n\\n## Targets\\n\\n- Send-like actions: `to: \\\"channel:<id>\\\"` or `to: \\\"user:<id>\\\"`.\\n- Message-specific actions: `channelId: \\\"<id>\\\"` (or `to`) + `messageId: \\\"<id>\\\"`.\\n\\n## Common Actions (Examples)\\n\\nSend message:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"send\\\",\\n  \\\"channel\\\": \\\"discord\\\",\\n  \\\"to\\\": \\\"channel:123\\\",\\n  \\\"message\\\": \\\"hello\\\",\\n  \\\"silent\\\": true\\n}\\n```\\n\\nSend with media:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"send\\\",\\n  \\\"channel\\\": \\\"discord\\\",\\n  \\\"to\\\": \\\"channel:123\\\",\\n  \\\"message\\\": \\\"see attachment\\\",\\n  \\\"media\\\": \\\"file:///tmp/example.png\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n- Optional `silent: true` to suppress Discord notifications.\\n\\nSend with components v2 (recommended for rich UI):\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"send\\\",\\n  \\\"channel\\\": \\\"discord\\\",\\n  \\\"to\\\": \\\"channel:123\\\",\\n  \\\"message\\\": \\\"Status update\\\",\\n  \\\"components\\\": \\\"[Carbon v2 components]\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n- `components` expects Carbon component instances (Container, TextDisplay, etc.) from JS/TS integrations.\\n- Do not combine `components` with `embeds` (Discord rejects v2 + embeds).\\n\\nLegacy embeds (not recommended):\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"send\\\",\\n  \\\"channel\\\": \\\"discord\\\",\\n  \\\"to\\\": \\\"channel:123\\\",\\n  \\\"message\\\": \\\"Status update\\\",\\n  \\\"embeds\\\": [{ \\\"title\\\": \\\"Legacy\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Embeds are legacy.\\\" }]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n- `embeds` are ignored when components v2 are present.\\n\\nReact:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"react\\\",\\n  \\\"channel\\\": \\\"discord\\\",\\n  \\\"channelId\\\": \\\"123\\\",\\n  \\\"messageId\\\": \\\"456\\\",\\n  \\\"emoji\\\": \\\"✅\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nRead:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"read\\\",\\n  \\\"channel\\\": \\\"discord\\\",\\n  \\\"to\\\": \\\"channel:123\\\",\\n  \\\"limit\\\": 20\\n}\\n```\\n\\nEdit / delete:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"edit\\\",\\n  \\\"channel\\\": \\\"discord\\\",\\n  \\\"channelId\\\": \\\"123\\\",\\n  \\\"messageId\\\": \\\"456\\\",\\n  \\\"message\\\": \\\"fixed typo\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"delete\\\",\\n  \\\"channel\\\": \\\"discord\\\",\\n  \\\"channelId\\\": \\\"123\\\",\\n  \\\"messageId\\\": \\\"456\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nPoll:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"poll\\\",\\n  \\\"channel\\\": \\\"discord\\\",\\n  \\\"to\\\": \\\"channel:123\\\",\\n  \\\"pollQuestion\\\": \\\"Lunch?\\\",\\n  \\\"pollOption\\\": [\\\"Pizza\\\", \\\"Sushi\\\", \\\"Salad\\\"],\\n  \\\"pollMulti\\\": false,\\n  \\\"pollDurationHours\\\": 24\\n}\\n```\\n\\nPins:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"pin\\\",\\n  \\\"channel\\\": \\\"discord\\\",\\n  \\\"channelId\\\": \\\"123\\\",\\n  \\\"messageId\\\": \\\"456\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThreads:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"thread-create\\\",\\n  \\\"channel\\\": \\\"discord\\\",\\n  \\\"channelId\\\": \\\"123\\\",\\n  \\\"messageId\\\": \\\"456\\\",\\n  \\\"threadName\\\": \\\"bug triage\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nSearch:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"search\\\",\\n  \\\"channel\\\": \\\"discord\\\",\\n  \\\"guildId\\\": \\\"999\\\",\\n  \\\"query\\\": \\\"release notes\\\",\\n  \\\"channelIds\\\": [\\\"123\\\", \\\"456\\\"],\\n  \\\"limit\\\": 10\\n}\\n```\\n\\nPresence (often gated):\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"set-presence\\\",\\n  \\\"channel\\\": \\\"discord\\\",\\n  \\\"activityType\\\": \\\"playing\\\",\\n  \\\"activityName\\\": \\\"with fire\\\",\\n  \\\"status\\\": \\\"online\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Writing Style (Discord)\\n\\n- Short, conversational, low ceremony.\\n- No markdown tables.\\n- Mention users as `<@USER_ID>`.\\n\"}],\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1772431957971}}\n/root/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/903e22d9-d9fa-4d72-8057-30ad4084055b.jsonl:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"fe6f0892\",\"parentId\":\"b739fc8d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T06:12:44.194Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"The discord skill shows me how to interact with Discord channels, but it doesn't define what \\\"onboarding\\\" a channel means. Let me think about what makes sense in this context:\\n\\n1. The user is asking me to \\\"onboard this channel\\\" - this could mean:\\n   - Setting up the channel for task management\\n   - Creating an initial welcome message\\n   - Configuring the channel for some specific purpose\\n   - Just introducing myself to the channel\\n\\nLooking at the available skills, I see there's a `discord-task-management` skill that might be relevant. Let me check that one as it might define what \\\"onboarding\\\" means in this context.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"reasoning_content\"},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_03aad787dd5442ffa9f6bd39\",\"name\":\"read\",\"arguments\":{\"path\":\"/root/.agents/skills/discord-task-management/SKILL.md\"}}],\"api\":\"openai-completions\",\"provider\":\"zai\",\"model\":\"glm-5\",\"usage\":{\"input\":1214,\"output\":158,\"cacheRead\":14464,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":15836,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"timestamp\":1772431957973}}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":21,"a