created but not populated. Bug in my script. Let me fix and also make it actually send to Discord:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_73345971da4f413499ee1b90","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/*.md 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"cli\\|message\\|send\" | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_912f7149bf5d48829e7b4125","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw --help 2>&1 | head -30"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":452,"output":472,"cacheRead":33344,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34268,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772512513033}}
{"type":"message","id":"a8026763","parentId":"7d512c38","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:35:29.618Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_73345971da4f413499ee1b90","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- You are debugging time formatting in messages or system prompt output\n## Message envelopes (local by default)\nInbound messages are wrapped with a timestamp (minute precision):\n[Provider ... 2026-01-05 16:26 PST] message text\nsame timezone selection as message envelopes (default: host-local).\n- [Messages](/concepts/messages)\n  <strong>Any OS gateway for AI agents across WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, iMessage, and more.</strong><br />\n  Send a message, get an agent response from your pocket. Plugins add Mattermost and more.\nOpenClaw is a **self-hosted gateway** that connects your favorite chat apps — WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, iMessage, and more — to AI coding agents like Pi. You run a single Gateway process on your own machine (or a server), and it becomes the bridge between your messaging apps and an always-available AI assistant.\n**Who is it for?** Developers and power users who want a personal AI assistant they can message from anywhere — without giving up control of their data or relying on a hosted service.\n  B --> D[\"CLI\"]\n    WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, and iMessage with a single Gateway process.\n    Isolated sessions per agent, workspace, or sender.\n    Send and receive images, audio, and documents.\n- If you **do nothing**, OpenClaw uses the bundled Pi binary in RPC mode with per-sender sessions.\n  messages: { groupChat: { mentionPatterns: [\"@openclaw\"] } },\n  <Card title=\"Channels\" href=\"/channels/telegram\" icon=\"message-square\">\nsummary: \"Logging overview: file logs, console output, CLI tailing, and the Control UI\"\n### CLI: live tail (recommended)\nUse the CLI to tail the gateway log file via RPC:"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":20,"aggregated":"- You are debugging time formatting in messages or system prompt output\n## Message envelopes (local by default)\nInbound messages are wrapped with a timestamp (minute precision):\n[Provider ... 2026-01-05 16:26 PST] message text\nsame timezone selection as message envelopes (default: host-local).\n- [Messages](/concepts/messages)\n  <strong>Any OS gateway for AI agents across WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, iMessage, and more.</strong><br />\n  Send a message, get an agent response from your pocket. Plugins add Mattermost and more.\nOpenClaw is a **self-hosted gateway** that connects your favorite chat apps — WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, iMessage, and more — to AI coding agents like Pi. You run a single Gateway process on your own machine (or a server), and it becomes the bridge between your messaging apps and an always-available AI assistant.\n**Who is it for?** Developers and power users who want a personal AI assistant they can message from anywhere — without giving up control of their data or relying on a hosted service.\n  B --> D[\"CLI\"]\n    WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, and iMessage with a single Gateway process.\n    Isolated sessions per agent, workspace, or sender.\n    Send and receive images, audio, and documents.\n- If you **do nothing**, OpenClaw uses the bundled Pi binary in RPC mode with per-sender sessions.\n  messages: { groupChat: { mentionPatterns: [\"@openclaw\"] } },\n  <Card title=\"Channels\" href=\"/channels/telegram\" icon=\"message-square\">\nsummary: \"Logging overview: file logs, console output, CLI tailing, and the Control UI\"\n### CLI: live tail (recommended)\nUse the CLI to tail the gateway log file via RPC:","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772512529614}}
{"type":"message","id":"ec8119a8","parentId":"a8026763","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:35:31.224Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_912f7149bf5d48829e7b4125","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.1 (2a8ac97) — Chat automation for people who peaked at IRC.\n\nUsage: openclaw [options] [command]\n\nOptions:\n  --dev                Dev profile: isolate state under ~/.openclaw-dev, default\n                       gateway port 19001, and shift derived ports\n                       (browser/canvas)\n  -h, --help           Display help for command\n  --log-level <level>  Global log level override for file + console\n                       (silent|fatal|error|warn|info|debug|trace)\n  --no-color           Disable ANSI colors\n  --profile <name>     Use a named profile (isolates\n                       OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR/OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH under\n                       ~/.openclaw-<name>)\n  -V, --version        output the version number\n\nCommands:\n  Hint: commands suffixed with * have subcommands. Run <command> --help for details.\n  acp *                Agent Control Protocol tools\n  agent                Run one agent turn via the Gateway\n  agents *             Manage isolated agents (workspaces, auth, routing)\n  approvals *          Manage exec approvals (gateway or node host)\n  browser *            Manage OpenClaw's dedicated browser (Chrome/Chromium)\n  channels *           Manage connected chat channels (Telegram, Discord, etc.)\n  clawbot *            Legacy clawbot command aliases\n  completion           Generate shell completion script\n  config *             Non-interactive config helpers (get/set/unset/file).\n                       Default: starts setup wizard."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1595,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.1 (2a8ac97) — Chat automation for people who peaked at IRC.\n\nUsage: openclaw [options] [command]\n\nOptions:\n  --dev                Dev profile: isolate state under ~/.openclaw-dev, default\n                       gateway port 19001, and shift derived ports\n                       (browser/canvas)\n  -h, --help           Display help for command\n  --log-level <level>  Global log level override for file + console\n                       (silent|fatal|error|warn|info|debug|trace)\n  --no-color           Disable ANSI colors\n  --profile <name>     Use a named profile (isolates\n                       OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR/OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH under\n                       ~/.openclaw-<name>)\n  -V, --version        output the version number\n\nCommands:\n  Hint: commands suffixed with * have subcommands. Run <command> --help for details.\n  acp *                Agent Control Protocol tools\n  agent                Run one agent turn via the Gateway\n  agents *             Manage isolated agents (workspaces, auth, routing)\n  approvals *          Manage exec approvals (gateway or node host)\n  browser *            Manage OpenClaw's dedicated browser (Chrome/Chromium)\n  channels *           Manage connected chat channels (Telegram, Discord, etc.)\n  clawbot *            Legacy clawbot command aliases\n  completion           Generate shell completion script\n  config *             Non-interactive config helpers (get/set/unset/file).\n                       Default: starts setup wizard.","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772512531217}}
{"type":"message","id":"f929675c","parentId":"ec8119a8","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:35:34.760Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check if there's a way to send messages via CLI.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1db6455a178545159d78f461","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw channels --help 2>&1"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fd25c718ebff477e8480480d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw agent --help 2>&1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":1184,"output":52,"cacheRead":33792,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35028,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772512531224}}
{"type":"message","id":"818ab422","parentId":"f929675c","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:35:36.653Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_1db6455a178545159d78f461","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.1 (2a8ac97) — Works on Android. Crazy concept, we know.\n\nUsage: openclaw channels [options] [command]\n\nManage connected chat channels and accounts\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help    Display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  add           Add or update a channel account\n  capabilities  Show provider capabilities (intents/scopes + supported features)\n  help          Display help for command\n  list          List configured channels + auth profiles\n  login         Link a channel account (if supported)\n  logout        Log out of a channel session (if supported)\n  logs          Show recent channel logs from the gateway log file\n  remove        Disable or delete a channel account\n  resolve       Resolve channel/user names to IDs\n  status        Show gateway channel status (use status --deep for local)\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw channels list\n    List configured channels and auth profiles.\n  openclaw channels status --probe\n    Run channel status checks and probes.\n  openclaw channels add --channel telegram --token <token>\n    Add or update a channel account non-interactively.\n  openclaw channels login --channel whatsapp\n    Link a WhatsApp Web account.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/channels"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1884,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.1 (2a8ac97) — Works on Android. Crazy concept, we know.\n\nUsage: openclaw channels [options] [command]\n\nManage connected chat channels and accounts\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help    Display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  add           Add or update a channel account\n  capabilities  Show provider capabilities (intents/scopes + supported features)\n  help          Display help for command\n  list          List configured channels + auth profiles\n  login         Link a channel account (if supported)\n  logout        Log out of a channel session (if supported)\n  logs          Show recent channel logs from the gateway log file\n  remove        Disable or delete a channel account\n  resolve       Resolve channel/user names to IDs\n  status        Show gateway channel status (use status --deep for local)\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw channels list\n    List configured channels and auth profiles.\n  openclaw channels status --probe\n    Run channel status checks and probes.\n  openclaw channels add --channel telegram --token <token>\n    Add or update a channel account non-interactively.\n  openclaw channels login --channel whatsapp\n    Link a WhatsApp Web account.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/channels","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772512536650}}
{"type":"message","id":"a4f8f182","parentId":"818ab422","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:35:38.665Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_fd25c718ebff477e8480480d","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.1 (2a8ac97) — iMessage green bubble energy, but for everyone.\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|feishu|nostr|msteams|mattermost|nextcloud-talk|matrix|bluebubbles|line|zalo|zalouser|synology-chat|tlon\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2001,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.1 (2a8ac97) — iMessage green bubble energy, but for everyone.\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|feishu|nostr|msteams|mattermost|nextcloud-talk|matrix|bluebubbles|line|zalo|zalouser|synology-chat|tlon\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772512538659}}
