{"type":"message","id":"e9bfe1ef","parentId":"27f466ac","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:38:28.758Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_49263010ab1a4d0d94be2019","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/prose.md:Direct URLs are fetched as-is. This uses the `web_fetch` tool (or `exec` for POST)."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":16,"aggregated":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/prose.md:Direct URLs are fetched as-is. This uses the `web_fetch` tool (or `exec` for POST).","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772512708754}}
{"type":"message","id":"80664c7b","parentId":"e9bfe1ef","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:38:28.774Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_71b0eaabc31f4988ba3dc8ce","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"Configuration overview: common tasks, quick setup, and links to the full reference\"\nread_when:\n  - Setting up OpenClaw for the first time\n  - Looking for common configuration patterns\n  - Navigating to specific config sections\ntitle: \"Configuration\"\n---\n\n# Configuration\n\nOpenClaw reads an optional <Tooltip tip=\"JSON5 supports comments and trailing commas\">**JSON5**</Tooltip> config from `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`.\n\nIf the file is missing, OpenClaw uses safe defaults. Common reasons to add a config:\n\n- Connect channels and control who can message the bot\n- Set models, tools, sandboxing, or automation (cron, hooks)\n- Tune sessions, media, networking, or UI\n\nSee the [full reference](/gateway/configuration-reference) for every available field.\n\n<Tip>\n**New to configuration?** Start with `openclaw onboard` for interactive setup, or check out the [Configuration Examples](/gateway/configuration-examples) guide for complete copy-paste configs.\n</Tip>\n\n## Minimal config\n\n```json5\n// ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n{\n  agents: { defaults: { workspace: \"~/.openclaw/workspace\" } },\n  channels: { whatsapp: { allowFrom: [\"+15555550123\"] } },\n}\n```\n\n## Editing config\n\n<Tabs>\n  <Tab title=\"Interactive wizard\">\n    ```bash\n    openclaw onboard       # full setup wizard\n    openclaw configure     # config wizard\n    ```\n  </Tab>\n  <Tab title=\"CLI (one-liners)\">\n    ```bash\n    openclaw config get agents.defaults.workspace\n    openclaw config set agents.defaults.heartbeat.every \"2h\"\n    openclaw config unset tools.web.search.apiKey\n    ```\n  </Tab>\n  <Tab title=\"Control UI\">\n    Open [http://127.0.0.1:18789](http://127.0.0.1:18789) and use the **Config** tab.\n    The Control UI renders a form from the config schema, with a **Raw JSON** editor as an escape hatch.\n  </Tab>\n  <Tab title=\"Direct edit\">\n    Edit `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` directly. The Gateway watches the file and applies changes automatically (see [hot reload](#config-hot-reload)).\n  </Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n## Strict validation\n\n<Warning>\nOpenClaw only accepts configurations that fully match the schema. Unknown keys, malformed types, or invalid values cause the Gateway to **refuse to start**. The only root-level exception is `$schema` (string), so editors can attach JSON Schema metadata.\n</Warning>\n\nWhen validation fails:\n\n- The Gateway does not boot\n- Only diagnostic commands work (`openclaw doctor`, `openclaw logs`, `openclaw health`, `openclaw status`)\n- Run `openclaw doctor` to see exact issues\n- Run `openclaw doctor --fix` (or `--yes`) to apply repairs\n\n## Common tasks\n\n<AccordionGroup>\n  <Accordion title=\"Set up a channel (WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, etc.)\">\n    Each channel has its own config section under `channels.<provider>`. See the dedicated channel page for setup steps:\n\n    - [WhatsApp](/channels/whatsapp) — `channels.whatsapp`\n    - [Telegram](/channels/telegram) — `channels.telegram`\n    - [Discord](/channels/discord) — `channels.discord`\n    - [Slack](/channels/slack) — `channels.slack`\n    - [Signal](/channels/signal) — `channels.signal`\n    - [iMessage](/channels/imessage) — `channels.imessage`\n    - [Google Chat](/channels/googlechat) — `channels.googlechat`\n    - [Mattermost](/channels/mattermost) — `channels.mattermost`\n    - [MS Teams](/channels/msteams) — `channels.msteams`\n\n    All channels share the same DM policy pattern:\n\n    ```json5\n    {\n      channels: {\n        telegram: {\n          enabled: true,\n          botToken: \"123:abc\",\n          dmPolicy: \"pairing\",   // pairing | allowlist | open | disabled\n          allowFrom: [\"tg:123\"], // only for allowlist/open\n        },\n\n[441 more lines in file. Use offset=101 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772512708765}}
{"type":"message","id":"22f7dd28","parentId":"80664c7b","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:38:42.507Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me take a simpler approach. I'll create a notification script that the AI can run, or I'll update the health check to write a notification file that gets picked up.\n\nActually, the simplest solution for now: update the cron to write output to a log file, and I (as the AI orchestrator) will read that log during quiet hours and send notifications.\n\nBut the user wants the cron to send notifications. Let me create a wrapper that uses sessions_spawn or calls back to the gateway.\n\nActually, let me just create a simple notification mechanism using a session. I'll use the main session to send notifications.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me create a simpler notification wrapper:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f1a772c053244927b01223de","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/health-check-notify.sh","content":"#!/bin/bash\n# Health check wrapper that sends Discord notification\n# Uses the main agent session to send via message tool\n\nSCRIPT_DIR=\"$(dirname \"$0\")\"\nLOG_FILE=\"/root/.openclaw/workspace/logs/nightly-health-check.log\"\n\n# Run health check and capture output\nOUTPUT=$(/usr/bin/python3 \"$SCRIPT_DIR/health-check.py\" --fix 2>&1)\necho \"$OUTPUT\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\n\n# Extract summary for Discord (last 10 lines)\nSUMMARY=$(echo \"$OUTPUT\" | tail -10)\n\n# Send notification via openclaw agent\n# Using the main session to send to #bytebles (health check notifications channel)\nopenclaw agent \\\n  --session-id \"health-check-notifier\" \\\n  --channel discord \\\n  --message \"System health check complete.\" \\\n  --deliver \\\n  --reply-channel discord \\\n  --reply-to \"channel:1478055780409278464\" \\\n  2>/dev/null || echo \"Notification failed (non-critical)\"\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":1078,"output":378,"cacheRead":42624,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44080,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772512708774}}
{"type":"message","id":"b2b29042","parentId":"22f7dd28","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:38:42.531Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f1a772c053244927b01223de","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 835 bytes to /root/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/health-check-notify.sh"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772512722521}}
{"type":"message","id":"99d0adee","parentId":"b2b29042","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:38:52.285Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Actually, that won't work well because the agent command doesn't have a way to send a custom message with the summary. Let me think of a different approach.\n\nThe cleanest solution is to have the orchestrator (which is me, the AI) handle notifications during quiet hours. The health check script creates folders and logs to ops.log. The orchestrator reads ops.log and sends a notification if there's something to report.\n\nBut for immediate cron-based notifications, I need a different approach. Let me create a simple script that writes to a notification queue file, and have the orchestrator pick it up and send.Actually, let me just update the cron to NOT send notifications, and update the policy so the orchestrator checks ops.log during quiet hours and sends a digest.Or I can use a Discord webhook. Let me check if Discord webhooks are configured.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5988294c915f495e839ae8c1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"webhook\" /root/.openclaw/ 2>/dev/null | head -5"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":457,"output":206,"cacheRead":43648,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44311,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772512722531}}
