2\\\">>>\"},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1772431820654}}\n/root/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/c0c333cd-bc6e-46e4-ac7f-a18340f950d0.jsonl:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"7d512c38\",\"parentId\":\"2067afbc\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T04:35:29.588Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Good progress! But I notice:1. acutis-flow only has the folder created, not the full structure - there's a bug in my script\\n2. The notification is just printed, not actually sent to DiscordLet me fix the script to:1. Handle the case where folder doesn't exist (create all structure)\\n2. Actually send the Discord notification via the OpenClaw API or a direct callActually, for the notification, the best approach is to have the script output JSON that the orchestrator can use, or call a webhook. Let me think about this...\\n\\nActually, the simplest approach is to have the script just log and fix, and let the orchestrator (during quiet hours) pick up the task and send notifications if needed. The user's design was for the orchestrator to do health checks during quiet hours, not a cron job.\\n\\nBut there IS a cron job. Let me ask: should the cron job send Discord notifications, or should that only happen when the orchestrator runs the health check?\\n\\nActually, the user said \\\"run the cron job manually\\\" and expected a Discord message. So the cron job should send notifications. Let me update the script to actually send to Discord.\\n\\nI can use the OpenClaw message tool via an HTTP call to the gateway, or I can output in a format that gets picked up. Let me check if there's a way to send messages from a script.\\n\\nActually, the simplest approach is to use the message tool directly here since I'm an AI with access to it. Let me run the script and then send the notification myself.\\n\\nOr better - update the cron entry to just run the fix, and have me (the AI) send the notification based on what was logged.\\n\\nBut actually, the user wants a fully automated solution. Let me check if OpenClaw has a CLI for sending messages.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"reasoning_content\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The acutis-flow folder was created but not populated. Bug in my script. Let me fix and also make it actually send to Discord:\"},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_73345971da4f413499ee1b90\",\"name\":\"exec\",\"arguments\":{\"command\":\"cat /usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/*.md 2>/dev/null | grep -i \\\"cli\\\\|message\\\\|send\\\" | head -20\"}},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_912f7149bf5d48829e7b4125\",\"name\":\"exec\",\"arguments\":{\"command\":\"openclaw --help 2>&1 | head -30\"}}],\"api\":\"openai-completions\",\"provider\":\"zai\",\"model\":\"glm-5\",\"usage\":{\"input\":452,\"output\":472,\"cacheRead\":33344,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":34268,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"timestamp\":1772512513033}}\n/root/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/c0c333cd-bc6e-46e4-ac7f-a18340f950d0.jsonl:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"0cfbc95f\",\"parentId\":\"7fb2862e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T04:38:08.282Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"The cron job is updated. But it doesn't send Discord notifications automatically. The notification should be sent by the orchestrator during quiet hours, not by the cron script.\\n\\nLet me think about this more holistically:\\n\\n1. **Ops.log pruning**: Cron at 00:00 UTC - DONE\\n2. **Health check**: Cron at 01:00 UTC - creates folders, logs to ops.log\\n3. **Discord notification**: Should this be part of the cron job or the orchestrator?\\n\\nThe user's design was for the orchestrator to pick from system tasks during quiet hours. The health check is a system task. The orchestrator would:1. Pick \\\"Health Check\\\" from system/tasks.md\\n2. Run it\\n3. Send a Discord notification if needed\\n\\nBut there's also a cron job. The question is: should the cron job send notifications, or should that be the orchestrator's job?\\n\\nI think the cleanest approach:- Cron job runs health check, fixes folders, logs to ops.log- Orchestrator (during quiet hours) reads ops.log and sends summary to Discord\\n\\nBut that's more complex. For now, let me add notification capability to the script using the OpenClaw CLI. Or I can have the script call a webhook.\\n\\nActually, let me check if there's a way to send via CLI or if I should use a different approach.\\n\\nThe user said they want a notification when the cron runs. So let me add notification support to the script using `openclaw agent --deliver`.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"reasoning_content\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The cron runs the script but doesn't send Discord notifications. Let me add that capability:\"},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_f6929cb937314535ae553c44\",\"name\":\"exec\",\"arguments\":{\"command\":\"openclaw agent --channel discord --reply-to \\\"channel:1478055780409278464\\\" --message \\\"Test from CLI\\\" --deliver 2>&1\"}}],\"api\":\"openai-completions\",\"provider\":\"zai\",\"model\":\"glm-5\",\"usage\":{\"input\":196,\"output\":380,\"cacheRead\":41344,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":41920,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"timestamp\":1772512671828}}","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772512732328}}
{"type":"message","id":"41e038bc","parentId":"3a9a9c27","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:39:05.364Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me simplify. I'll use OpenClaw's cron system with `delivery.mode = \"announce\"` to send to Discord. This is the cleanest approach according to the docs.\n\nI'll create a cron job that:\n1. Runs the health check script\n2. Uses the built-in announce delivery to send results to Discord\n\nActually, looking at the docs, the `announce` delivery is for isolated agent turns, not for running scripts. The script runs via shell cron.\n\nLet me take a different approach: create a Discord webhook URL that the script can POST to. Or I can have the script write to a queue file and the orchestrator sends during quiet hours.\n\nFor now, the simplest working solution is:\n1. Cron runs health check, fixes folders, logs to ops.log\n2. During quiet hours, the orchestrator reads ops.log and sends a daily digest to Discord\n\nLet me update the policy to reflect this, and remove the notification wrapper script.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me simplify this. The cleanest approach per the docs is to use OpenClaw's built-in cron with announce delivery. Let me convert this:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_41fc4a05ba804a43ad07ad2a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"rm /root/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/health-check-notify.sh 2>/dev/null; openclaw cron add \\\n  --name \"Health Check\" \\\n  --cron \"0 1 * * *\" \\\n  --tz \"UTC\" \\\n  --session isolated \\\n  --message \"Run health check: python3 /root/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/health-check.py --fix. Then summarize what was done.\" \\\n  --announce \\\n  --channel discord \\\n  --to \"channel:1478055780409278464\" \\\n  2>&1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":12052,"output":361,"cacheRead":44096,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56509,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772512732338}}
{"type":"message","id":"5b8b3473","parentId":"41e038bc","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:39:07.998Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_41fc4a05ba804a43ad07ad2a","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"id\": \"44819451-6288-4ad9-a73c-3292e2c40c7f\",\n  \"name\": \"Health Check\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"createdAtMs\": 1772512747900,\n  \"updatedAtMs\": 1772512747900,\n  \"schedule\": {\n    \"kind\": \"cron\",\n    \"expr\": \"0 1 * * *\",\n    \"tz\": \"UTC\"\n  },\n  \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n  \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n    \"message\": \"Run health check: python3 /root/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/health-check.py --fix. Then summarize what was done.\"\n  },\n  \"delivery\": {\n    \"mode\": \"announce\",\n    \"channel\": \"discord\",\n    \"to\": \"channel:1478055780409278464\"\n  },\n  \"state\": {\n    \"nextRunAtMs\": 1772586000000\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2619,"aggregated":"{\n  \"id\": \"44819451-6288-4ad9-a73c-3292e2c40c7f\",\n  \"name\": \"Health Check\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"createdAtMs\": 1772512747900,\n  \"updatedAtMs\": 1772512747900,\n  \"schedule\": {\n    \"kind\": \"cron\",\n    \"expr\": \"0 1 * * *\",\n    \"tz\": \"UTC\"\n  },\n  \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n  \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n    \"message\": \"Run health check: python3 /root/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/health-check.py --fix. Then summarize what was done.\"\n  },\n  \"delivery\": {\n    \"mode\": \"announce\",\n    \"channel\": \"discord\",\n    \"to\": \"channel:1478055780409278464\"\n  },\n  \"state\": {\n    \"nextRunAtMs\": 1772586000000\n  }\n}","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772512747990}}
