{"type":"message","id":"d230d32b","parentId":"4291bdc2","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:58:24.653Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f16c0b5d1b4442cb8e96a7e4","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-02-experiments-changelog.md:user: [Mon 2026-03-02 05:55 UTC] Define Orchestrator Planning Algorithm In /system/policy.md, define orchestrator loop: For selected domain: Read purpose.md Read manual.md Read activity.log Read recent Discord messages Read queued messages for domain Decide ONE highest-leverage action If active hours: Queue proposal or action message If quiet hours: Perform experimentation or optimization only Log result in: domain activity.log system ops.log\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-02-experiments-changelog.md:| **Policy** | `system/policy.md` — loops, quiet hours, nagging doctrine, orchestrator |\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-02.md:Updated `system/policy.md` with detailed orchestrator behavior:\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-03-orchestrator-design.md:user: [Mon 2026-03-02 15:49 UTC] So the purpose of the cron job and the orchestrator is to run every 15 minutes, and the main purpose of the orchestrator is to, through a round-robin work on, I think it runs every 15 minutes and it takes one channel at a time, and the goal is to help move the final of the conversation towards its purpose. So during the active hours, that means asking strategic questions. The questions could be filling in gaps, asking for status from the user, or anything like that. And in the off hours, it's thinking, it's organizing artifacts, running experiments, looking at patterns, looking at the previous day's activity, looking for weekly patterns, those kinds of things\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-03-orchestrator-design.md:assistant: Let me check my memory for any prior context about this orchestrator system.\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-03-orchestrator-design.