uld be filling in gaps, asking for status from the user, or anything like that. And in the off hours, it's thinking, it's organizing artifacts, running experiments, looking at patterns, looking at the previous day's activity, looking for weekly patterns, those kinds of things\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-03-orchestrator-design.md:assistant: Let me check my memory for any prior context about this orchestrator system.\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-03-orchestrator-design.md:assistant: Got it. So the orchestrator is a **pulse-based channel nudge system**:\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-03-orchestrator-design.md:4. **Where should this live?** — A skill? A cron-configured orchestrator script? Something the heartbeat system triggers?\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-03-orchestrator-design.md:assistant: Found it. Already has orchestrator structure — I'll update it with the clarifications you gave.\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/system/policy.md:   - `system/ops.log` — previous orchestrator runs\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/system/policy.md:Before orchestrator proposes any action for a domain:","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772513904642}}
{"type":"message","id":"e70f16cc","parentId":"d230d32b","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:58:34.959Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the orchestrator is mentioned in the policy and memory, but it doesn't seem to exist as an actual cron job or script yet. The user said \"the orchestrator that runs every 5 minutes\" but looking at the policy, it says:\n\n```\n| Loop | Interval | Action |\n|------|----------|--------|\n| Heartbeat | ~30s | Send due messages only |\n| Orchestrator | ~15m | Select one domain, perform one best action |\n```\n\nSo the orchestrator should run every 15 minutes, not 5. And there's no cron job for it. It looks like this is something that was designed but never actually implemented.\n\nLet me check if there's a script or if this is supposed to be part of the heartbeat system.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_77f43a08482b49dfb4d58286","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-03-orchestrator-design.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":1116,"output":192,"cacheRead":56640,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57948,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772513904653}}
{"type":"message","id":"3af2e089","parentId":"e70f16cc","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:58:34.973Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_77f43a08482b49dfb4d58286","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session: 2026-03-03 03:34:33 UTC\n\n- **Session Key**: agent:main:main\n- **Session ID**: 9d88d33c-ac61-4115-850c-7f11e1fd5e97\n- **Source**: gateway:sessions.reset\n\n## Conversation Summary\n\nuser: [Mon 2026-03-02 15:49 UTC] So the purpose of the cron job and the orchestrator is to run every 15 minutes, and the main purpose of the orchestrator is to, through a round-robin work on, I think it runs every 15 minutes and it takes one channel at a time, and the goal is to help move the final of the conversation towards its purpose. So during the active hours, that means asking strategic questions. The questions could be filling in gaps, asking for status from the user, or anything like that. And in the off hours, it's thinking, it's organizing artifacts, running experiments, looking at patterns, looking at the previous day's activity, looking for weekly patterns, those kinds of things\nassistant: Let me check my memory for any prior context about this orchestrator system.\nassistant: Got it. So the orchestrator is a **pulse-based channel nudge system**:\n\n| Phase | Behavior |\n|-------|----------|\n| **Active hours** | Conversational — one strategic question per channel per pulse, filling gaps, checking status |\n| **Off hours** | Reflective — organize artifacts, run experiments, analyze patterns (daily/weekly) |\n\n**Round-robin** = one channel per 15-min tick, not all channels every tick. Keeps it lightweight and spreads attention.\n\nA few clarifying questions:\n\n1. **Active hours definition** — What's the window? (e.g., 09:00–21:00 IST? Or per-channel preferences?)\n\n2. **Channel selection** — Round-robin across *all* Discord channels, or only ones with active/pending conversations?\n\n3. **\"Strategic questions\" scope** — Is this reading each channel's `purpose.md` + recent messages and deciding what to ask? Or more structured (e.g., pre-defined question templates)?\n\n4. **Where should this live?** — A skill? A cron-configured orchestrator script? Something the heartbeat system triggers?\n\nI'll capture the core design in memory once we lock in the details.\nuser: [Mon 2026-03-02 15:53 UTC] So the quiet hours is midnight India time to 5 a.m. India time, and everything else after that is considered active hours . So the channel selection is round robin across all Discord channels with no exception Yes, it has to read the channel's purpose and recent messages, and all the everything it has access to that's related to that particular channel. So it shouldn't read the content for other channels, but it should read system-wide messages and it should read the previous logs of what it did previously, just so that it doesn't keep repeating the same thing. Basically, it should come up with a single question to move the channel's conversation one step closer to its purpose. This could be like filling in gaps or asking questions about a particular project, any of these types of things . Look for a file, I think there is a policy.md file somewhere. All of this should go there in that file, all of these instructions should go there\nassistant: Found it. Already has orchestrator structure — I'll update it with the clarifications you gave.\nassistant: Let me consolidate — there's now some duplication between the two sections.\nassistant: Done. Updated `system/policy.md` with:\n\n**Orchestrator behavior:**\n- **Active (05:00–00:00 IST):** Round-robin all Discord channels, one per tick → one strategic question to move conversation toward purpose\n- **Quiet (00:00–05:00 IST):** Organize, experiment, analyze patterns, prep briefs\n\n**Context isolation:**\n- Reads channel-scoped files + system-wide files\n- Does NOT read other channels' content\n\n**Anti-repetition:**\n- Reads `activity.log` and `ops.log` to avoid re-asking\n\nWant me to set up the cron job for this, or is there infrastructure already in place?\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772513914967}}
{"type":"message","id":"0bbadaea","parentId":"3af2e089","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:58:48.194Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the orchestrator was designed in the policy but never actually implemented as a cron job or script. The user is asking me to trigger it manually, but it doesn't exist yet. I need to create it.\n\nThe orchestrator should:\n1. Run every 15 minutes\n2. Select one Discord channel in round-robin\n3. During active hours (05:00-00:00 IST): Ask one strategic question to move conversation toward purpose\n4. During quiet hours (00:00-05:00 IST): Organize, experiment, analyze patterns\n\nLet me create this as an OpenClaw cron job with an isolated session.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"The orchestrator was designed in the policy but never actually created as a cron job. Let me set it up:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_18dd5b7493524a4fa5716b31","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron add \\\n  --name \"Orchestrator\" \\\n  --cron \"*/15 * * * *\" \\\n  --tz \"UTC\" \\\n  --session isolated \\\n  --message \"ORCHESTRATOR TICK: Read system/policy.md for rules. Select next channel in round-robin. Check current time (IST). If active hours (05:00-00:00 IST): read channel purpose.md, recent messages, activity.log - formulate ONE strategic question to move conversation toward purpose, send via message tool. If quiet hours (00:00-05:00 IST): pick task from system/tasks.md or channel tasks.md, execute silently. Log action to system/ops.log and channel activity.log.\" \\\n  --announce \\\n  --channel discord \\\n  --to \"user:729703087031320577\" \\\n  2>&1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":1121,"output":349,"cacheRead":57728,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59198,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772513914973}}
